  "analysis": "The critical finding is `system.file(\"include\", package=\"BH\")` returns an empty string, so RStan cannot find Boost headers even though the `BH` package is installed. This may be because the apt `r-cran-bh` package installs headers in a non-standard location or `system.file` is failing. We need inspect the `BH` installation directory structure and possibly reinstall `BH` from CRAN source so the include path is correct.",
